I"!<p>When you are fearful and anxious, you begin to think differently. Bringing awareness to these thought patterns can help you recognise when you are caught in anxiety.</p>

<h1 id="tunnel-vision">Tunnel Vision</h1>

<p>Focusing only only the negative aspects of your experience and ignoring the positive.</p>

<h1 id="catastrophising">Catastrophising</h1>

<p>Expecting the worst case scenario to happen.</p>

<h1 id="mind-reading-and-fortune-telling">Mind reading and fortune telling</h1>

<p>Assuming you know what other people are thinking and often assuming other peopleâ€™s perceptions of you are or will be negative.</p>

<h1 id="emotional-reasoning">Emotional reasoning</h1>

<p>Assuming that because you feel strongly towards a situation it must be the only reflection of how things are.</p>
